TLDR; I think i finally found something to control the migraines I’m always complaining about that prevent me from living a regular life 🙂

I’ve been migraine free for over a month. That hasn’t happened in about 5+ years. I know it could be too soon to know whether or not this medication will continue to prevent them, but I’ve had one every single month for so long that going a month and a half feels like a miracle

I found a website online that pairs you with a doctor and you’re able to get prescription medication specifically for migraines. I was prescribed something about a month and a half ago and the few times I felt a migraine coming I’d take the medication and it would go away.

I was unable to afford a visit to a doctor to find a solution. I’ve tried so many things to try and get them under control so my life wouldn’t revolve around “will I have a migraine today that will ruin my plans”. They would affect conventions, seeing friends and family, etc

A lot of you know that I get sick. A LOT. It’s usually severe and debilitating migraines that I get every month and my only relief is sleeping for several days until it’s gone. These migraines have seriously affected my life for the last few years and without health insurance-
